The paper deals with the computational power of accessing information sources in different orders, which is a topic closely related to computational complexity. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of the polynomial hierarchy, which is a fundamental concept in computational complexity theory, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as likely sub-categories. The paper also involves mathematical proofs, suggesting cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the study of information theory, suggesting cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible sub-category.
